<dl id="n36013b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36013b">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36013b"> 13(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> glacis</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The great wall of Delhi, which was constructed by Shah Jahan, was strengthened by the English by the addition of a ditch and <mark>glacis</mark>, after Delhi was captured by Lord Lake in 1803; and its strength was turned against the British at the time of the Mutiny. <small> &ldquo;DELHI&rdquo; <a name="EBDH" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBDH"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 954d</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
